\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 153. C. aspera} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 916 (1753) ({\i C. heterophylla} Willd.). Stems 20-50 cm, erect, much-branched, often white-tomentose below. Leaves green, scabrid; lower usually divided; upper entire to sinuate-dentate, mucronate, sometimes with auriculate base. Capitula solitary. Involucre (10-)15-25 mm in diameter, ovoid to globose; bracts pale reddish, indistinctly veined; appendages small, patent or deflexed, usually with 3-5 palmately arranged, divergent or parallel spines. Florets purple, the outer slightly patent. Achenes c. 4 mm, whitish, with reddish stripes; pappus 1-2 mm, reddish. 2n = 22.{\i  Dry, open habitats. • S.W. Europe, extending eastwards to C. Italy.} Bl Ga Hs It Lu Sa.
