\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b aspera}: Stems up to 50 cm, erect or ascending, much-branched. Lower leaves oblong-lanceolate, pinnatifid to sinuate-dentate; upper linear-lanceolate. Involucre c. 20 mm in diameter, globose; appendages half as long as bract, with 3-5 divergent, yellow spines, the apical longer. {\i Throughout the range of the species}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b stenophylla} (Dufour) Nyman,{\i  Consp.} 432 (1879) ({\i C. stenophylla} Dufour): Stems up to 50 cm, erect, branched. Leaves green to grey-tomentose; lower pinnatifid to deeply dentate; upper narrowly linear to filiform, the margin revolute, entire or remotely dentate at base. Involucre 6-15 mm in diameter, ovoid; appendages with 3 divergent, equal, palmate spines.{\i  E. Spain} ({\i S. of Valencia}),{\i  S. Portugal} ({\i Algarve}).
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b scorpiurifolia} (Dufour) Nyman, {\i loc. cit.} (1879) ({\i C. scorpiurifolia} Dufour): Stems c. 20 cm, simple or sparingly branched. Leaves undivided, entire to serrate; lower oblong-ovate, acuminate. Involucre 10-15 mm in diameter, ovoid; appendages with 3-5 divergent spines.{\i  S. Spain}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b d}) Subsp. {\b pseudosphaerocephala} (R. J. Shuttlew. ex Rouy) Gugler, {\i Centaur. Ung. Nationalmus.} 214 (1907): Stems up to 60 cm, erect, sparingly branched. Lower leaves oblong, pinnatifid to lobed; upper linear-lanceolate. Involucre 20-25 mm in diameter, globose; appendages with 3(-5) parallel spines. {\i S. France}.
\par 

